  "storySummary": "started their journey as a Half-Elf Wizard with the Acolyte background.",
  "lastNarrative": "Dawn spills a pale gold across the endless plains, the grass whispering under a gentle breeze that carries the faint scent of wild herbs. You lie on the soft earth, the cool dew soaking your cloak, and the world feels both new and strangely familiar. In the distance, the low, mournful howl of an unseen creature rolls over the hills to the southeast, a sound that prickles the hair on the back of your neck. A lone, shadowy figure stands motionless near a lone oak at the edge of the plain, its features indistinct but unmistakably watching you. To the north, the plains stretch into a hazy line where the horizon blurs into mist; southward, the jungle looms, dense and dark, while the distant hills rise like silent sentinels. An uneasy curiosity tugs at you – how did you come to this place, and what calls from those far hills?\n\nYou might:\n1. Scan the immediate area, perhaps using a spell like *detect magic* or simply looking for clues about your arrival.\n2. Approach the unknown figure to see if it offers any answers or aid.\n3. Follow the direction of the howl toward the hills, hoping to uncover the source before night falls.\n\nThe morning air is crisp, the world alive with possibility, yet the distant howl reminds you that unknown dangers may already be stirring.",
